This paper deals with the intersection of machine learning and game theory, which is a common topic in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes an algorithm for feature selection, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS). The use of game theory in the algorithm also suggests a potential connection to computational economics (cs.CE) and cryptography (cs.CR).
